      "writtenOn": "2021-06-01T07:31:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We discussed this offline.\n\nLet me rephrase my concern. Let\u0027s say we have an exported utility function in a support library, e.g.\n\n package somelib\n\n func SomeFunc(ctx context.Context) error\n\nIf we allow accessing runtime variables defined in test/fixture/service metadata via context.Context, SomeFunc *might* do this and fail if the current test/fixture/service don\u0027t declare certain runtime variables. SomeFunc accepts certain Contexts but not other Contexts. This is something I think it\u0027s nice to avoid.\n\nThis problem won\u0027t be solved even we split the accessor function to ContextTestVar/ContextFixtVar/ContextBundleVar.",
      "parentUuid": "68494074_a4d5d08d",
